2. Design Goals & Non-Goals
Design Goals
1.  Durable Execution: Zero lost work. If the server power cycles, the agent must resume the deal
analysis at Step 3 of 5 [A][C].
2.  Local Sovereignty: 80%+ of inference tokens must be generated locally. No dependency on internet
for core deal triage [A][B].
3.  Audit-Grade Observability: Every decision, tool call, and state change must be logged, traceable,
and replayable [C].
4.  Safety-First Tooling: No destructive action (delete, send email) occurs without an explicit policy
 check or human approval [A].
Non-Goals
*  Massive Scale: We are designing for hundreds of high-value deals per day, not millions of consumer
requests. Latency and correctness trump throughput [B].
*  No-Code Config: This is a code-first engineering platform. We prioritize developer control over
drag-and-drop agent builders.
*  Generic Chat: This is not a chatbot. It is a job-to-be-done automation engine.
